337
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:18,340
Why is this space a place for a lot of queer

338
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:20,420
and marginalized people in the first place?

339
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:23,860
Why does his work resonate so well

340
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:28,820
with people who the man himself would have hated even more

341
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:30,500
than he hated everyone else?

342
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:37,540
Now, I don't think I'm qualified to answer this question.

343
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:40,580
I don't actually think anyone really is.

344
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:43,140
There's probably a lot of different reasons,

345
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:46,580
but from what I can gather,

346
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:50,100
it seems like the answer lies in the specifics

347
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,100
of how Lovecraft saw the world,

348
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:55,460
in the place that his approach actually came from.

349
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:57,300
"'When Lovecraft was three years old,

350
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:58,500
his father had a breakdown

351
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:00,100
and was committed to a mental hospital.

352
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,700
He died there five years later.

353
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,340
His mother also frequently suffered from similar problems

354
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:06,740
and later died in the same hospital.

355
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:10,100
Lovecraft suffered from periods of severe anxiety and depression.

356
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:11,540
He had to drop out of high school

357
00:23:11,540 --> 00:23:14,340
and often isolated himself for long periods at a time.

358
00:23:14,340 --> 00:23:16,660
He saw himself as a temporary visitor

359
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:18,660
to a strange and unwelcoming world.

360
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:21,860
This is present even in one of Lovecraft's earliest stories,

361
00:23:21,860 --> 00:23:23,140
The Outsider.

362
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:26,420
The narrator escapes from being trapped within a decaying castle,

363
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:28,820
but his search for human contact is frustrated

364
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:31,380
when the people he finds run away in horror.

365
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:34,340
He turns and sees a detestable and ghoulish creature

366
00:23:34,340 --> 00:23:35,700
has entered the room.

367
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:39,060
